&lt;p&gt;
	The conditions found at the time of the inspection were not typical of the normal conditions maintained at the establishment and arose because:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The designated Senior Cook was on long term sick and key data management documents that record management, inspection and monitoring information (Safer Food Better Business Pack) could not be found and thus could not be viewed at inspection. The inspection reported that a folder was found and that it was blank; this is true but was not the current and active Safer Food pack which was located shortly after the inspection concluded. The management of data and the Safer Food pack has been reviewed and addressed; a new Safer Food pack has been created with a newly appointed Senior Cook. The newly appointed Senior Cook is working closely with centre management and all other cooks/kitchen staff to implement a far reaching programme of improvement. This includes ensuring compliance with current directives as requested at inspection along with other current advice from Govt and Food Standards agencies. All staff involved with Food have&amp;nbsp; booked to retake level 2 Food Hygiene with the Senior Cook undertaking Level 3. All other schedule A issues have been addressed and all&amp;nbsp; B recommendations have been adopted. We welcome and are booking reinspection at the earliest opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;

